notes: This inscription commemorates the restoration of a road from Carthage to the borders of Numidia by Emperor Maximinus Thrax and his son Maximus Caesar. The dating to 237 CE corresponds to Maximinus' third year of tribunician power. The road had fallen into disrepair through long neglect (longa incuria corruptam atque dilapsam). Maximinus held the titles Germanicus maximus, Sarmaticus maximus, and Dacicus maximus, reflecting military victories. His son Maximus held the same victory titles and was designated as heir with the titles nobilissimus Caesar and princeps iuventutis.
